Directions:
What You'll Need Blondies: 1/2 cup (1 stick) butter, softened; 1 egg. Streusel: 1-1/2 tbsp butter, melted. Caramel Sauce: 1/2 tbsp melted butter; 1 tbsp milk. Heat oven to 375 degrees F. Spray 8 x 8-inch baking pan with cooking spray. Beat butter and blondie mix in medium bowl on medium-high speed until mixture resembles fine crumbs. Add eggs; mix until soft dough forms. Press dough evenly into pan. Stir streusel mix and melted butter in small bowl. Sprinkle evenly on dough. Bake 20 to 22 minutes until golden brown. Cool completely. Prepare the caramel sauce: Stir 1/2 tbsp melted butter, caramel sauce mix and milk in medium microwave-safe bowl or 4-cup glass measuring cup. Microwave 1 to 1-1/2 minutes until bubbly throughout and slightly thickened. Caution: Bowl will be hot. Stir and drizzle immediately over cooled blondies. Sprinkle and desired amount of salt.
